### Solution Process
Let $O$ be the center of the hyperbola.  Since $AB$ is parallel to the y-axis and passes through $F_2$, $AB$ is a vertical line of symmetry of the hyperbola, and $O$ is the midpoint of both $\overline{AB}$ and $\overline{F_1F_2}$.

[asy]
unitsize(0.4 cm);

pair A, B, F1, F2, O;

A = (5,5);
B = (5,-5);
F1 = (-10,0);
F2 = (10,0);
O = (F1 + F2)/2;

