label("$F_1$", F1, SW);
label("$F_2$", F2, SE);
label("$O$", O, S);
[/asy]

Since $O$ is the midpoint of $\overline{AB}$, $|AO| = |BO| = \frac{1}{2} |AB| = 5$.  Since $O$ is the midpoint of $\overline{F_1 F_2}$, $|F_1 O| = |F_2 O| = c$ for some $c > 0$.  By the definition of a hyperbola, $|F_1 A| - |F_2 A| = 2a$, so
\[13 - |F_2 A| = 2a.\]Then $|F_2 A| = 13 - 2a$.  By the Pythagorean Theorem on right triangle $F_2 AO$,
\[c^2 + 5^2 = (13 - 2a)^2.\]By the Pythagorean Theorem on right triangle $F_1 AO$,
\[c^2 + 5^2 = 13^2.\]Then $(13 - 2a)^2 = 13^2$, so $13 - 2a = \pm 13$.  Since $a > 0$, $13 - 2a = -13$, so $a = 13$.  Then $c^2 = 13^2 - 5^2 = 144$, so $c = 12$.  The eccentricity of the hyperbola is then $\frac{c}{a} = \boxed{\frac{12}{13}}$.

